It's my birthday today and I'm exepecting to get a wish from her but I know she won't wish me. She was my love and I still love her a lot. I remember everything about her she is really innocent, cute, charming, understanding and have a big heart. But i lost her, she is gorgeous in every ways. She is so perfect that I will love her from far and I'll always wait for her no matter what.  Now she is with someone else living with her dream guy and I'm happy about her. At least she got someone who priotise her and respect her decision. This verse 4:43 exactly represents my feeling towards her. Just want to tell you My love that I'm never going to forget your memories, I will always revisit my hidden gallery where we both are smiling at each other, sharing each others emotion. snippet.textDisplay:
There are a thousand things I wish I had said before, but I never found the right time or maybe I was just too late. Today, I don’t want to hide anything. This is my last note to you, and I want it to carry the truth of my heart.
I still remember the day you first held my hand. I pretended it was nothing, blamed the cold, but inside my heart was trembling. That small moment lives inside me even now. I remember how I proposed, looking into your eyes, and how your yes,  became the happiest sound I had ever heard.
I remember the little things you did for me, the perfume you gave me that still holds your scent. Sometimes I catch it, and it feels like you’re still here beside me. Even now, after all this time, your presence hasn’t left me it lingers in every memory, in every corner of my heart.
And I will never forget that night you drunk-called me. Your voice was weak, trembling, and I was on the edge of tears. That night, I was ready to give you everything my whole heart, every piece of myself that I had spent years putting back together. In that moment, all of me belonged to you.
But , I failed to fix things when I had the chance. I should have fought harder, held on tighter, loved you better. I regret every moment I wasted, every silence I kept when I should have spoken, every distance I let grow between us. If I could turn back time, I would do it all differently. I would never let you slip away.
Now you are gone, but your memories still stay. Your love, your care they are no longer mine, yet they live in me like shadows I cannot escape. And what hurts the most is knowing that someone else may now hold your hand, kiss your lips, and stand in the place I once called mine. I was your first kiss,  I always wanted to be your last.
People tell me to move on, but how can I? My heart still whispers your name in the quiet. A part of me still hopes that one day maybe not now, maybe years from now you might return. But even if you don’t, even if our roads never cross again, the truth will remain the same.
I still love you. I always will. And my biggest regret will forever be that I realized the value of what we had too late

snippet.textDisplay:
It’s strange how a song can change the air around me. One moment I am just listening, and the next—boom—memories flood in. Suddenly, I am back in places I thought I had left behind, faces reappear, voices echo. Dreams I once carried, fragile and beautiful, rise again like they were never lost.

The song becomes more than music; it becomes a doorway. A doorway to unfinished chapters, to pages I could never complete. Words I once held inside, moments I wished I had lived longer, stories that ended too soon—all of them come rushing back.

And in that moment, I feel both full and empty. Full of everything I once lived, empty because I can’t go back and rewrite those pages. The song lingers, and so do the pieces of me scattered in memories, dreams, and half-written stories...❤
